title: ld: error: undefined symbol: git_branch_name_is_valid
body:
I am trying to upgrade the FreeBSD port ```devel/gitui``` to 0.17 but it fails:
```
error: linking with `cc` failed: exit status: 1
  |
  = note: "cc" "-m64" "-Wl,--eh-frame-hdr" "-Wl,-znoexecstack" "-Wl,--as-needed" "-L" "/usr/local/lib/rustlib/x86_64-unknown-freebsd/lib" "/disk-samsung/freebsd-ports/devel/gitui/work/target/release/deps/gitui-02c0d335be5b4ef3.gitui.b5kpi5f1-cgu.0.rcgu.o" "-o" "/disk-samsung/freebsd-ports/devel/gitui/work/target/release/deps/gitui-02c0d335be5b4ef3" "-Wl,--gc-sections" "-pie" "-Wl,-zrelro" "-Wl,-znow" "-nodefaultlibs" "-L" "/disk-samsung/freebsd-ports/devel/gitui/work/target/release/deps" "-L" "/usr/local/lib" "-L" "/usr/local/lib" "-L" "/disk-samsung/freebsd-ports/devel/gitui/work/target/release/build/openssl-sys-76af8282e9fa888f/out/openssl-build/install/lib" "-L" "/disk-samsung/freebsd-ports/devel/gitui/work/target/release/build/sys-info-5822cae94de9cb44/out" "-L" "/usr/local/lib/rustlib/x86_64-unknown-freebsd/lib" "-Wl,-Bstatic" "/tmp/rustc2gn2UM/libsys_info-89e5367ff0be931c.rlib" "/tmp/rustc2gn2UM/libopenssl_sys-5ba2f78aea990f5d.rlib" "-Wl,--start-group" "-Wl,--end-group" "/usr/local/lib/rustlib/x86_64-unknown-freebsd/lib/libcompiler_builtins-46641b4a03e19e40.rlib" "-Wl,-Bdynamic" "-lpthread" "-lgit2" "-lssh2" "-lz" "-lrt" "-lutil" "-lexecinfo" "-lutil" "-lexecinfo" "-lpthread" "-lgcc_s" "-lc" "-lm" "-lrt" "-lpthread" "-lrt" "-lutil" "-lutil" "-fstack-protector-strong" "-L/usr/local/lib"
  = note: ld: error: undefined symbol: git_branch_name_is_valid
          >>> referenced by gitui.b5kpi5f1-cgu.0
          >>>               /disk-samsung/freebsd-ports/devel/gitui/work/target/release/deps/gitui-02c0d335be5b4ef3.gitui.b5kpi5f1-cgu.0.rcgu.o:(gitui::app::App::draw_popups::ha6ceb7bac26063ba)
          cc: error: linker command failed with exit code 1 (use -v to see invocation)
          

error: aborting due to previous error

error: could not compile `gitui`
```

rust-1.53.0
FreeBSD 13
